# PersonalFinance

Persian RTL personal + business finance app. Source of truth: `REQUIREMENTS.md`, `ARCHITECTURE.md`, `ROADMAP.md`.

**Stack:** Java 21 · Spring Boot 3 · PostgreSQL · Flyway · Next.js (TypeScript) · Tailwind  
**Domain rules:** Toman (integer, no decimals) · Jalali dates in UI/API · Gregorian `DATE` in DB · server is source of truth

---

## Project layout

```
PersonalFinance/
├── backend/          # Spring Boot (Maven)
│   └── src/main/java/com/personalfinance/{module}/
│       ├── controller/
│       ├── service/
│       ├── repository/
│       ├── entity/
│       └── dto/
├── frontend/         # Next.js (migrating from Vite/React)
└── ROADMAP.md        # Milestone order is authoritative; do not skip ahead
```

One backend package per domain module (`account`, `auth`, `income`, `loan`, `expense`, …). Phase 2 modules follow the same pattern (`product`, `counterparty`, `inventory`, …).

---

## Naming

| Layer | Convention | Example |
|-------|------------|---------|
| Java packages | lowercase, singular module | `com.personalfinance.account` |
| Java classes | PascalCase | `AccountService`, `AccountRequest` |
| REST paths | kebab-case, plural | `/api/v1/pending-expenses` |
| DB tables/columns | snake_case | `pending_expenses`, `created_at` |
| Flyway files | `V{n}__snake_description.sql` | `V7__add_receivables.sql` |
| DTOs | `{Entity}Request` / `{Entity}Response` | `AccountRequest` |
| Enums (Java + TS) | `UPPER_SNAKE` | `DIGITAL_WALLET` |
| TS files | camelCase | `accountsApi.ts`, `jalaliUtils.ts` |

User-facing labels (account names, categories, counterparties) are **never hardcoded** — only system enums and UI copy are fixed.

