## Next.js frontend

> **Migration note:** Legacy Vite/React code lives in `frontend/src/`. New work targets Next.js App Router. Preserve API contracts and visual tokens during migration.

**Recommended structure:**
```
frontend/
├── app/                  # App Router — routes, layouts, route groups
│   ├── (auth)/login/
│   ├── (app)/            # Protected routes
│   └── layout.tsx        # dir="rtl" lang="fa"
├── features/             # Feature modules (accounts, investments, …)
│   └── {feature}/
│       ├── components/
│       ├── api.ts
│       └── types.ts
├── shared/               # Cross-feature UI (buttons, modals, date picker)
├── lib/                  # API helpers, auth utilities, config
├── hooks/                # Shared React hooks
├── types/                # Shared TypeScript types
└── tailwind.config.ts    # Design tokens — single source for colors/fonts
```

**Rules:**
- RTL everywhere: `dir="rtl"` `lang="fa"`, Vazirmatn font. Date inputs display LTR (`dir="ltr"`) for `YYYY/MM/DD`.
- API client: native `fetch` with `credentials: 'include'`. Parse `ApiResponse<T>` via shared helper in `lib/`.
- Do not duplicate server state in global stores. Use TanStack Query for server state when available.
- Auth: check session via `GET /api/v1/auth/me` on load; redirect unauthenticated users to `/login`. No dev auth bypass in production code.
- Styling: Tailwind with project design tokens (`brand-dark`, `brand-accent`, `surface`, `text-primary`, …).
- Prefer shadcn/ui for reusable UI components. Avoid introducing additional UI libraries unless explicitly approved.
- UI copy: Persian. Amounts: comma-formatted via `numberFormat`. Enum labels: `Record<Enum, string>` maps.
- Each backend module maps to a `features/{module}/` folder and one or more routes under `app/(app)/`.
- API base URL via Next.js env (`NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` or rewrites) — do not hardcode ports in components.

